    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.8.0-dev-1088-gbd4eca114\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nLinux Mint 20.2\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nKitty 0.15\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nappimage\r\n\r\n### How to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n1. `nvim --clean repro.lua`\r\n2. Paste the following Lua code:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.cmd[[\r\nset undofile\r\ninoremap . .<C-g>u]]\r\n\r\nlocal function command_preview(opts, _, _)\r\n  vim.cmd(\"norm i\" .. opts.args)\r\n  return 0\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command(\"Test\", function() end, { preview = command_preview, nargs = 1 })\r\n```\r\n3. `:so %`\r\n4. Type `:Test a.a.a.a.a.`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe buffer text should not change because `0` is returned from the preview callback indicating that no preview should be shown. The undo file should not be corrupted.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nPreviewing the command has two unwanted side effects:\r\n1. The buffer text is modified and `a.a.a.a.a.a.a.a.a.a.` is inserted (this change also can't be undone by pressing `u`).\r\n2. Undoing the changes manually, then trying to source the file results in the following error: \r\n```\r\nError detected while processing /home/user/repro.lua:                                                        \r\nE5113: Error while calling lua chunk: /home/user/test.lua:4: Vim(set):E825: Corrupted undo file (num_head): /home/j\r\nonas/.local/state/nvim/undo/%home%user%repro.lua\r\nstack traceback:\r\n        [C]: in function 'cmd'\r\n        /home/user/repro.lua:4: in main chunk\r\n```",
